4 February 2021 Figtree Community Hall 11 Princes Highway , Figtree
**Program starts:** 4/02/2021 -_ **Program Postponed, new start date to be
Beat It Lite is a FREE 9 week physical activity and lifestyle program
delivered by an Accredited Exercise Physiologist. This life-changing program
can help you get back into a healthy routine to better manage your diabetes.
Whether you have exercised before or need some help getting started, the Beat
It Lite program will help you on your journey to a healthier and more active
life. The Exercise Physiologist will tailor individual exercises to your
specific needs within a friendly and supportive environment.
"This program is the greatest gift to someone living with diabetes who may
need a helping hand to get back on track."
1.Bookings are essential as there are limited places available. Book online now, or call the NDSS Helpline on 1800 637 700.
2.Look out for your starter pack in the mail, and get your Medical Clearance form signed by your GP before your initial consultation.
3.Attend your 45min initial consultation with your Beat It Trainer before the 9 week program starts.
4.Attend your group exercise sessions and education sessions for the duration of the 9 week program.
 **This program is FREE for NDSS registrants who have not participated in a
face-to-face Beat It program within the last 2 years.**
We’ve implemented new measures to protect the safety and wellbeing of all
attendees and staff at our diabetes events. Read about our new safety measures
_The National Diabetes Services Scheme (NDSS) is an initiative of the
Australian Government and is administered by Diabetes Australia. The NDSS
agent in NSW & ACT is Diabetes NSW & ACT. Find out more about the NDSS at
ndss.com.au or call the NDSS Helpline on 1800 637 700._
